posts.title: Since 2020, I have lost multiple decades long friendships because I support Donald Trump. It has been a true blessing from God.
posts.content:
The oldest friend apologized for his bad behavior a few months ago. I forgave him, and we are slowly beginning to rebuild things, with politics being off limits.

Another husband and wife team (the wife was the problem) is odd. The husband and I act like nothing is wrong on the very rare occasions when we see each other, and we went to the funeral of the wife’s brother recently. My wife took food over a week later, but has not been as “all in” as I have seen her in the past. She says she hasn’t forgotten how they didn’t reach out when she was in the hospital. She doesn’t hate them, but she doesn’t forgive them.

Another friend and I just haven’t spent time together. We finally got together for a nice meal, and I refused to discuss politics as he was itching for a fight and I wasn’t.

The last was a friend of my wife’s who just stopped talking because of politics. My wife grieved that one more than I did - I think my wife did more of the giving there, but if it made her happy, I didn’t mind.

I almost lost my wife to Covid back in December of 2021. They wanted to ventilate her, and I was able to “violate hospital protocol” and smuggle Ivermectin in which saved her life. (Within 24 hours of her taking it, they stopped trying to put her on a ventilator.) We have two children, and the friendships I’m talking about were ones I had always believed would “be there” for us during times of trouble.

They were nowhere to be found. There may have even been some “should have gotten vaxed” talk but not to my face. I struggled with that for a while, until I realized what a gift from God their absence truly was —

Imagine if they had stuck around, and I had LISTENED to them. I know they would have advised me to “do what the doctors said” and if I had been weak enough to do that (and there were times of fear and despair where I might have) there is No Question In My Mind that My Wife Would Be Dead.

I will not lie and say I haven’t grieved those relationships, felt anger and sorrow and rage and betrayal, you name it, I’ve felt it and sometimes even wallowed in self pity over it, BUT their absence in my life was a Gift from God, and the fact I didn’t realize it at the time didn’t make it any less true.

The days ahead are going to be challenging. There are people I can talk to about politics, and people I can’t. I’ve learned who I can trust - God, my wife and my children - and that everyone else is optional.

I am and remain a lucky and blessed man.

Just a reminder, in case others need it.
